1. See above, p. 16. Since this work is not a treatise on geography but an attempt at historical synthesis, | will mention in this and the following chapters only those names that are of some significance in the history of events or dynasties. A discussion of the various opinions put forth on the location of the geographic names of Ptolemy can be found in Roland Braddell, “Study of Ancient Times in the Malay Peninsula,” JRASMB, XIII (1935).

