The old pronunciation of the character fo, which commonly was used to transcribe the word buddha, is b'iuat, which is an acceptable way of rendering bhadra. On the other hand hu ta is pronounced huo d’at, which would be a much less satisfactory transcription. The equation of Fan Fo with Bhadravarman resolves the difficulty.

