these epithets is extremely doubtful, for they constitute sorts of puns, playing on the meanings of the component parts of the geographic terms. Thus, to cite only two examples, Talaittakkolam is called “praised by great men versed in the sciences” because in Tamil kalai = science and takkor — scholar, and Valaippandiru is described as “possessing both cultivated and uncultivated land” because vilaippu = sowing and tdru = bush,

